<div align="center" class="about-text">
    <p class ="media-heading">Our school</p><br>
    <p>Fathima Muslim Ladies’ College, a leading academic institution today was inaugurated in 1918 by honorable Justice M.T. Akbar with the unstinted support of Sir Razik Fareed, A.H. Macan Markar, Dr. Bathiudeen Mahmood, M.I.M. Haniffa, and W.M. Abdul Rahman through the education Muslim Society under the banner of Fathima Muslim Girls’ English School. The school begun with just 40 students and faculty of 5 teachers at Old Moors’ Street for the purpose of educating the Muslim women. It was found that more accommodation was required for the incoming students and in 1920 it was shifted to Silver Smith Lane, now named Bandaranayake Mawatha. Today almost 100 years later, Fathima Muslim Ladies’ College has a student population of 2700 and 112 teachers. The progress has resulted in with Fathima Muslim Ladies College reaching a preferred school status.

        The school has had a progressively successful history with excellent professionals being presented to the world in internationally accepted fields including art, commerce and science</p>
